main.title: Severe Storms this Week Possible from the Plains to the Midwest
main.teaserTitle: Severe Storms this Week Possible from the Plains to the Midwest

seometa.title: Severe Storms this Week Possible from the Plains to the Midwest | The Weather Channel

main.description: Meteorologist Ari Sarsalari looks at the forecast for severe weather this week.
main.transcript: well we're in a very active part of the severe weather season and we're gonna see this in the next couple days especially in the plains although through the overnight we've also got to watch out for some severe storms in parts of the mid Mississippi River valley we've already had storms there throughout Monday I could have another round or 2 before all is said and done at least during this time period but those storms that form out in the plains especially parts of Nebraska and South Dakota those could produce some pretty large hail none of this stuff looks like we're gonna have widespread tornadoes or anything we could see a tornado or 2 but damaging straight line wind and hail is going to be the number one threat okay with these storms now we got another chance for severe weather once again in the plains especially western Kansas Nebraska eastern Colorado that'll be on Tuesday and then Wednesday yet another shot for some severe weather down in the lower Mississippi River valley and then Thursday actually kind of a different system here that will likely produce a more widespread severe weather a little bit of a better chance at maybe a little bit of a nastier overall severe weather events so stay tuned on that so we'll highlight Thursday there and keep in mind and in the meantime just a lot of rain will be falling so if you live in some of the spots that get storm after storm if you're unlucky enough to see that you could see some flooding as well
